title: The Southern Star (1968 - UK) [Orson Welles] Africa adventure
description:
The Southern Star (1968 - UK, France)

Adventure / Comedy / Crime

novel by . . . . Jules Verne
director . . . . Sidney Hayers, Orson Welles
starring . . . . George Segal, Ursula Andress, Orson Welles
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0065025/


Filmed at Niokolakoba National Park, Senegal    |    London, England, UK

Fortune hunter Dan Rockland comes to West Africa pretending to be a geologist. He is actually employed by Kramer, whose business is diamonds, and when Kramer's workers discover a huge uncut gem, Rockland is sent to retrieve it. He and his African guide Matakit have opposition to contend with, first from Capt. Karl Ludwig, who is Kramer's security chief, and another is the diabolical Plankett, who resents Rockland's interest in a woman named Erica. The jewel is brought to Kramer and named The Southern Star, but at a party to celebrate the find, a power blackout leads to chaos.
